tags.name: options.variations
tags.description: For convenience, the scorer can augment documents by replacing certain words with other words and phrases. This mechanism is called variations. This keys of this map are words that should be replaced, and the values are the replacement words or phrases.  For example, if you add a document whose only phrase is "firefox update", normally the scorer will register only this single phrase for the document.  However, if you pass the value `new Map(["firefox", ["fire fox", "fox fire", "foxfire"]])` for this parameter, it will register 4 total phrases for the document: "fire fox update", "fox fire update", "foxfire update", and the original "firefox update".

comments.description: Builds the phrase tree based on the current documents. The phrase tree lets us efficiently match queries against phrases.  Each path through the tree starting from the root and ending at a leaf represents a complete phrase in a document (or more than one document, if the same phrase is present in multiple documents).  Each node in the path represents a word in the phrase.  To match a query, we start at the root, and in the root we look up the query's first word.  If the word matches the first word of any phrase, then the root will have a child node representing that word, and we move on to the child node.  Then we look up the query's second word in the child node, and so on, until either a lookup fails or we reach a leaf node.
